in California (due to weatheraltered coastal sea floors that fooled surfers), and changes in salmon populations.
In addition, the east coast of the United States has experienced warmer and wetter springtime conditions, increasing the mosquito population and encephalitis cases.
Changing weather patterns have driven mice, and therefore snakes into Montana, increasing snake bite incidents.
Cooler and wetter springtime conditions in New Mexico have led to a rise in bubonic plague as the rodent population increased.
