Schematic of the main processes thought to produce El NiÃ±o.
Above-normal sea surface temperatures produce increased pr ecipitation and changes in atmospheric circulation.
These tend to maintain the warm temperatures by driving oceanic currents.
Some of these effects are immediate; others act after the forced signal reflects from the western boundary and returns to the region of strong coupling.
