The rate of deforestation varies from region to region.
Recent research results showed that in the Brazilian Amazon, the rate of deforestation was around 6200 square miles per year from 1978-1986, but fell to 4800 square miles per year from 1986-1993.
By 1988, 6% of the Regrowth Brazilian Amazon had been cut down (90,000 square miles, an Undisturbed area the size of New England).
