The net effect of smoke particles is a slight cooling at the Earth's surface.
Habitat fragmentation has destroyed the habitats required of many species of animals.
Desertification is a complex land degradation process involving man, land and climate.
Desertification reduces both resilience and productive potential of the land to an extent that can neither be readily reversed by removing the cause, nor easily reclaimed.
