18.
Bright red areas indicate areas of high relief.
19.
Vegetation absorbs carbon dioxide from the atmosphere and gives off oxygen.
It releases moisture through evapotranspiration.
When vegetation dies and decays the biomass is oxidized and carbon dioxide is released.
20.
The remote sensing established a relationship between the rate of emission of thermal radiation from the fire and the rate of emission of smoke.
